# Deployment Guide

The server is a single-process FastAPI/uvicorn app with no database and no persistent storage. All state is in-memory, which is fine for PoC use.

## Quick start with Docker (local)

```bash
cp .env.example .env   # fill in your keys
docker compose up --build
curl http://localhost:8000/health
```

---

## Option 1: Render (easiest — recommended for PoC)

Render auto-detects the `Dockerfile` and `render.yaml` in the repo.

1. Push the repo to GitHub.
2. Go to https://dashboard.render.com → **New → Web Service**.
3. Connect your GitHub repo.
4. Render detects `render.yaml` and pre-fills the settings. Click **Create Web Service**.
5. In the Render dashboard, go to **Environment** and fill in the secret values marked `sync: false`:
   - `OPENAI_API_KEY`
   - `DIFY_WEATHER_API_KEY` (and any other Dify tool keys)
6. Render builds the Docker image and deploys. Your URL will be `https://<service-name>.onrender.com`.
7. Point Agora ConvoAI at: `https://<service-name>.onrender.com/chat/completions`

**Note:** The free tier sleeps after 15 min of inactivity, causing a cold-start delay. Upgrade to a paid instance type for production.

