## Option 2: AWS Lightsail / EC2 (VM with systemd)

A `deploy/custom-llm.service` systemd unit is already included.

### Launch the instance

- Lightsail: Ubuntu 22.04, at least **1 GB RAM** (t3.micro or Lightsail $7/mo bundle).
- EC2: Ubuntu 22.04 AMI, `t3.micro` or larger.
- Open inbound port **8000** in the security group/firewall (or 80/443 if you add Nginx).

### Install on the server

```bash
# Install Python 3.11
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y python3.11 python3.11-venv python3-pip git

# Clone and set up
sudo mkdir -p /opt/custom-llm
sudo git clone <your-repo-url> /opt/custom-llm
cd /opt/custom-llm
python3.11 -m venv .venv
.venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt

# Configure environment
sudo cp .env.example .env
sudo nano .env          # fill in all keys

# Install and start systemd service
sudo cp deploy/custom-llm.service /etc/systemd/system/
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable custom-llm
sudo systemctl start custom-llm

# Check logs
sudo journalctl -u custom-llm -f
```

### Add HTTPS with Nginx + Let's Encrypt (recommended)

```bash
sudo apt install -y nginx certbot python3-certbot-nginx

# Create Nginx config
sudo tee /etc/nginx/sites-available/custom-llm <<'EOF'
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name your-domain.com;
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        # Required for SSE streaming
        proxy_buffering off;
        proxy_cache off;
        proxy_read_timeout 300s;
    }
}
EOF

sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/custom-llm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx
sudo certbot --nginx -d your-domain.com
```

